{"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.15","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.14","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.13","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.12","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.11","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.10","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.9","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.8","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.7","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.6","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.5","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.4"],"generated":true}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.16"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are no steps needed to migrate to 1.16 of the Composable Architecture, but there has been"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a change to the underlying behavior of "},{"code":".appStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" that one should be aware of. When using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".appStorage"},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Shared"},{"text":", if your key does not contain the characters “.” or “@”, then changes","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to that key in "},{"code":"UserDefaults","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be observed using key-value observing (KVO)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Otherwise, ","type":"text"},{"code":"NotificationCenter","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be used to observe changes.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KVO is a far more efficient way of observing changes to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UserDefaults"},{"type":"text","text":" and it works cross-process,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"such as from widgets and app extensions. However, KVO does not work when the keys contain “.”","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"or “@”, and so in those cases we must use the cruder tool of "},{"code":"NotificationCenter","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". That is not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as efficient, and it forces us to perform a thread-hop when the notification is posted before"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"we can update the ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" value. For this reason it is not possible to animate changes that are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"made directly to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UserDefaults"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["withAnimation {","  \/\/ ⚠️ This will not animate any SwiftUI views using '@Shared(.appStorage(\"co.pointfree.count\"))'","  UserDefaults.standard.set(0, forKey: \"co.pointfree.count\")","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In general, we recommend using other delimeters for your keys, such as “\/”, “:”, “-”, etc.:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["@Shared(.appStorage(\"co:pointfree:count\")) var count = 0"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"article","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","title":"Migrating to 1.16"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":".appStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" strategy used with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Shared"},{"text":" now uses key-value observing instead of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NotificationCenter"},{"type":"text","text":" when possible. Learn how this may affect your code."}],"references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture/MigratingTo1.9":{"role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.9","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.9","abstract":[{"text":"Update your code to make use of the new ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TestStore\/send(_:assert:fileID:file:line:column:)-8877x"},{"text":"","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"method on ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestStore"},{"type":"text","text":" which gives a succinct syntax for sending actions with case key paths, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer\/dependency(_:)"},{"text":" method for overriding dependen